11/05/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Greek Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis and Romanian President Traian Basescu praised the state of bilateral ties Tuesday (10 May), during a meeting held within the framework of the South-East European Co-operation Process summit in Bucharest. Karamanlis said Greece was happy to see Romania and Bulgaria seal the EU Accession Treaty and looks forward to greeting them as full members of the Union. Basescu, in turn, thanked Greece for its continued support. (Rompres - 11/05/05; Nine o'clock - 10/05/05)
